%N A393953 Decimal expansion of Product_{p prime} ((1 - 1/(p+1)^2) * (1 - 1/(p^2+1)^2)).
%C A393953 The asymptotic probability that the greatest common infinitary divisor of two positive integers selected independently at random is a fourth power (A000583).
%C A393953 In general, the asymptotic probability that the greatest common infinitary divisor of two positive integers selected independently at random is a 2^m-power is Product_{p prime} Product_{k=0..m-1} (1 - 1/(p^(2^k)+1)^2).
%F A393953 Equals A065472 * Product_{p prime} (1 - 1/(p^2+1)^2).
%F A393953 Equals A065472 * zeta(4)^2 * Product_{p prime} (1 - 3/p^4 + 2/p^6).
%F A393953 Equals zeta(4)^2 * Product_{p prime} (1 - 1/p^2 + 2/p^3 - 6/p^4 + 4/p^5).
%e A393953 0.735919176675180664442827052201056739215767277163158...
%o A393953 (PARI) prodeulerrat(1 - 1/(p+1)^2) * prodeulerrat(1 - 1/(p^2+1)^2)
%Y A393953 Cf. A000583, A013662, A065472, A077609, A183031.
%Y A393953 The asymptotic probability that the greatest common infinitary divisor of two positive integers selected independently at random is: A065472 (square), A393948 (1), A393949 (prime), A393950 (squarefree), A393951 (Fermi-Dirac prime), A393952 (exponentially 2^n-number), this constant (4th power).
%K A393953 nonn,cons
%O A393953 0,1
